The paper discusses session types, which are a type system for communication-based programs. This falls under the area of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also presents an executable semantics for a functional session type calculus, which involves formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The paper discusses concurrency and communication protocols, which are topics in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also presents an implementation in Agda, which is a functional programming language used for formal verification (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses linearity and recursion, which are topics in formal languages (cs.FL).
